The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, October 14, 2002  Calcutta Column
				 																																									Not so long ago, college common rooms were a place of attraction among students where they could gossip, play indoor games, and read magazines. At present, because of the tight academic schedule, students get little time to themselves. The concept of leisure is fast disappearing. Many colleges have discontinued with the common room facility. As a result they are falling prey to the all-play-no-work syndrome. 				 																																									Piyal Mukherjee, 				 																																									Lake Town.				 																																									We went to Gariahat for Puja shopping. The agent at the car parking lot charged us Rs 8 while issuing a receipt for Rs 5. Our protest fell on deaf ears.				 																																									Govinda Bakshi,				 																																									Budge Budge.
